The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 24: Inflation rose to 0.37 per cent during the second week of September from 0.12 per cent a week ago. Overall prices of raw food items climbed 15.64 per cent during the week ended September 12 year-on-year, driven mainly by a 44.85 per cent rise in vegetable prices. Potatoes turned costlier by 75 per cent, pulses 21 per cent and rice 17 per cent.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 24: The RBI has asked banks to assess the risk of real estate companies and their subsidiaries as a whole while giving loans as some of these firms have substantial investment in their subsidiaries.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 24: Jet Airways has secured shareholders approval to raise up to $400 million. The decision was taken at the companys extraordinary general meeting held today.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 24: An employee has no inherent right to voluntary retirement as the same is subject to the rules framed by the employer governing the scheme, the Supreme Court has ruled.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 24: SAIL is confident that the dispute over the renewal of four mines in Chiria will be resolved soon with the Jharkhand government acknowledging mining rights in the companys favour, chairman S.K. Roongta said.                                                                                                                           
